  "description": "Nightmare at Crack Axle Canyon (formerly known as Nightmare At Phantom Cave and Starchaser) was an enclosed Jet Star roller coaster at Six Flags Great Escape and Hurricane Harbor in Queensbury, New York.  The relatively simple steel coaster, manufactured by Anton Schwarzkopf, was enclosed in a dark warehouse-like building, giving a heightened sense of speed and disorientation around sharp twists and turns.  The ride was located in the park's Old West-themed Ghosttown area.",
